data.title: Udham Singh
data.meta_description: Udham Singh. Udham Singh, commonly known as Shaheed (Martyr) Udham Singh was a revolutionary from Punjab, India belonging to the Ghadar Party, best known for his assassination in London of Michael O' Dwyer, the former lieutenant governor of the Punjab in India, on 13 March 1940. He appeared as an extra in Alexander Korda's British movies Elephant Boy (1937) & Four Feathers (1939).
